While coding a Node.js application, I ran across the following issue:
By typing something like that

``` javascript
bot.send('sendMessage', {
  chat_id: data.message.chat.id,
  text: 'Oh, hello! :D Consider executing /help. ;)'
});
```

and placing the cursor onto the first open parenthesis, atom thinks that the closing parenthesis inside the string (in `;)`) is closing first one.
Obviously, that's not the case, because the second one is inside a string.
